This paper is primarily focused on computer vision, specifically on face parsing using deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and recurrent neural networks (RNNs). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of CNNs and RNNs for image segmentation and classification, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of the proposed algorithm for real-time applications, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
